 action or died later as a result of wounds received 45 cadets were wounded  What was cadet life like during the war  See these online collections of cadet letters and diaries  What did a New Market cadet uniform look like  This portrait of New Market Cadet Benjamin Colonna provides the best depiction of the cadet uniform  What kind of weapon did a New Market cadet carry   Of the 257 VMI cadets participating in the battle  around 200 carried the Austrian Lorenz rifle  the remainder carried the Model 1851 Cadet Springfield musket  I read about Cadet William McDowell in The Ghost Cadet  but it s a work of fiction  Where can I find out more about the real William McDowell  We have all available information about Willie McDowell on our Ghost Cadet Resources site  How old were the cadets who fought at New Market   Although the ages ranged from 15 to 25  most cadets were between 17 and 21 years old  that is  very similar in age to today s college students  The youngest cadet was Lewis S  Davis  15 years  0 months  28 days  the oldest was James S  Larrick  25 years  8 months  16 days  Where can I find a list of New Market cadets   Use our Online Rosters Database  type the search term New Market in the keyword search box  Do you have a map of the battlefield  This map was created by battle veteran Benajmin Colonna after extensive research  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 